80	 personal life marriage and lesbian affairs  in  she married eugene jan boissevain then the year-old widower of inez milholland. boissevain greatly supported her career and took primary care of domestic responsibilities. they lived in austerlitz new york at a farmhouse they called steepletop. the marriage was an open one and neither was faithful among her lovers was the poet george dillon fourteen years her junior for whom a number of her sonnets were written. millay also collaborated with dillon on flowers of evil translations of the poems of charles baudelaire from les fleurs du mal.  :  
